commit.message:
fix - regression on handling the cassette name in a class that inherits from unittest.TestCase
The cassette name did not include the class name if it inherits from unittest.TestCase, use the attribute "request.cls" to get the class instead of relying on "hasattr".

Use custom HTTP server for testing

www.iana.org stopped accepting multiple simultaneus connections,
which made tests fail: https://travis-ci.org/ktosiek/pytest-vcr/jobs/491821286.

commit.message:
Fix --vcr-record-mode deprecation warning

Without these changes, the `--vcr-record-mode` deprecation warning would
also be displayed when using the non-deprecated `--vcr-record` option.
Additionally it raised the warning in a deprecated way.

```
--vcr-record-mode has been deprecated and will be removed in a future release. Use --vcr-record instead.

test_no_warnings.py::test_method
  unknown file:0: RemovedInPytest4Warning: config.warn has been deprecated, use warnings.warn instead
```

Add a test to verify pytest-vcr isn't raising warnings where it shouldn't

This test currently fails because the test has two warnings:

```
--vcr-record-mode has been deprecated and will be removed in a future release. Use --vcr-record instead.

test_no_warnings.py::test_method
  unknown file:0: RemovedInPytest4Warning: config.warn has been deprecated, use warnings.warn instead
```
Release 1.0.0
